<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Espouse" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Espouse,</orth> vb. 1) to marry, to unite by the marriage-ceremony: <cit><quote>I have performed my task and was --d,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 9</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to take to wife: <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.81" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.5.18" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 5, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.242" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 242</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.242" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 242</bibl>
<lb /><emph>Espoused to</emph> == joined, associated with: <cit><quote>kings might be --d to more fame,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 20" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 20</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>and so --d to death,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.6.26" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 6, 26</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>